  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study was designed to obtain some baseline data on COPD in Malatya region of Turkey.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Sixty clusters from urban and rural regions were randomly selected. Ten and seven consecutive
      houses were included in the study from each urban and rural cluster respectively. A validated
      questionnaire on epidemiology of COPD was completed for each household over 18 by a pulmonary
      physician. Each subject performed the standard spirometric measurement and early
      bronchodilation testing.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
